# SQA-Test-Task

---
Welcome to Leobardo Vizcarra's SQA Test Task project. This is a simple test project that uses a layer-based
architecture, Java and Rest-Assured Library for writing its tests and, finally, TestNG Framework to run them.

## Objective

---
This project aims to verify the correct functionality of the **https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/** API by making use
of its endpoints via HTTP requests.

## Project Installation

---

### Requirements

In order to run the project, the following tools and programs are required:

* Windows 10
* [Java JDK 21](https://www.oracle.com/mx/java/technologies/downloads/#jdk21-windows)
* [IntelliJ IDEA 2024.3.3](https://www.jetbrains.com/idea/download/?section=windows) or better
* [Fork version 2.5.0.0](https://git-fork.com/) or better
* TestNG bundled Plugin v243.24978.46
* Connection with Internet access

### Cloning the SQA-Test-Task project

Open Fork and click the "File" menu option.

![FileOption](data:image/png;base64,)

Click the "Clone" menu option.

![CloneOption](data:image/png;base64,)

Paste the following link in the "Repository Url" text field `https://github.com/Vizcarreitor/SQA-Test-Task.git`

![ConfirmDialog](data:image/png;base64,)

Select your desired directory path in "Parent Folder" and click the "Clone" Button.

## Project Setup

---

Open IntelliJ IDEA and click the "Open" button.

![OpenOption](data:image/png;base64,)

Now look for the directory path where you cloned the project.

![ProjectDirectory](data:image/png;base64,)

Click the "OK" button.

### How to run tests

The project contains two test suites, the first one located in `src/test/java/critical.path`; the second one in
`src/test/java/critical.path`. In order to run them, go to the desired test suite class and simply click the "Run Test" button (TestNG Plugin required) next to the test/test suite.

![RunTest](data:image/png;base64,)
